text: Arizona's 3rd Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated entirely in northwest Pima County. As of 2018 there are 41 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 88,875. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Sally Ann Gonzales (D) and in the House of Representatives by Andrés Cano (D) and Alma Hernandez (D). ==See also== * List of Arizona Legislative Districts * Arizona State Legislature ==References== Category:Pima County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 3rd legislative district
